Nice — overall the file is solid and the logic works, but I’ll point out small issues and give you a cleaner modal-style version that behaves like a pop-up (overlay, lazy-load iframe after unlock, ESC to close, focus trap basics, prevent body scroll). Fixes & improvements included:

Issues / notes in your original

  • overflow: hidden on body prevents any scrolling site-wide — fine for full-screen popups but might bite if you only want a popup over content.

  • contactPageContent is position: absolute and z-index: 10. That’ll cover the page when shown, but better use position: fixed for true viewport coverage and a backdrop.

  • You load the iframe immediately (even while hidden). If you want privacy / performance, better set the src only after correct code.

  • No keyboard support (Esc to close) or focus management — accessibility improvements recommended.

  • Make sure ../pages/contact-owner.html path is correct relative to where this HTML is served. If it’s wrong, iframe will 404.

  • CryptoJS CDN is fine (you used 4.2.0). Optionally use SRI or host it yourself.

قال ChatGPT:

Got you — if you want that <iframe> to lock the background scroll when it appears, you gotta make it do two things:

  1. Prevent the body from scrolling while it’s open.

  2. Restore scroll when it’s gone.

Here’s your fixed and drop-in version 👇
(it auto-locks scroll when the iframe is added, and releases it if you remove it)

html
<style>
  body.no-scroll {
    overflow: hidden;
  }
</style>

<script>
  // create iframe element
  const iframe = document.createElement('iframe');
  iframe.src = "../pages/contact-owner.html";
  iframe.style.position = "fixed";
  iframe.style.inset = "0";
  iframe.style.width = "100%";
  iframe.style.height = "100%";
  iframe.style.border = "none";
  iframe.style.zIndex = "9999";
  iframe.style.background = "#fff"; // optional, just makes sure it’s solid

  // lock scroll when iframe opens
  document.body.classList.add('no-scroll');
  document.body.appendChild(iframe);

  // optional: example close function
  window.closeIframe = function () {
    iframe.remove();
    document.body.classList.remove('no-scroll');
  };
</script>

🧠 How it works

  • As soon as the iframe appears, body.no-scroll gets added → disables scrolling behind it.

  • When you call closeIframe() (from a button inside the iframe or main page), it removes the iframe and restores scroll.

If you want to trigger it with a button:

html
<button onclick="openContact()">فتح صفحة التواصل</button>

<script>
function openContact() {
  const iframe = document.createElement('iframe');
  iframe.src = "../pages/contact-owner.html";
  Object.assign(iframe.style, {
    position: "fixed",
    inset: "0",
    width: "100%",
    height: "100%",
    border: "none",
    zIndex: "9999",
    background: "#fff"
  });
  document.body.classList.add('no-scroll');
  document.body.appendChild(iframe);

  iframe.addEventListener("load", () => {
    iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("close-popup", () => {
      iframe.remove();
      document.body.classList.remove('no-scroll');
    });
  });
}
</script>

Now when that iframe is visible — boom, background’s frozen. No scrolling, no weird movement.

قال ChatGPT:

Got it — you want the scroll lock handled automatically by the iframe itself, without needing extra JS on the parent page.

Here’s how you can do it both ways (depending on what’s easier for you):

🧩 Option 1 — Do it directly with inline JS inside the iframe tag

This version locks scroll as soon as the iframe loads, and re-enables it when it’s removed:

html
<iframe
  src="../pages/contact-owner.html"
  style="position:fixed; inset:0; width:100%; height:100%; border:none; z-index:9999;"
  onload="document.body.style.overflow='hidden'; this.addEventListener('load',()=>{document.body.style.overflow='hidden';}); this.addEventListener('remove',()=>{document.body.style.overflow='';});"
></iframe>

✅ Simple, no edits inside contact-owner.html
⚠️ But the remove event doesn’t always fire reliably — so this is a quick hack, not bulletproof.

🧩 Option 2 — Put it inside contact-owner.html (cleaner & more reliable)

At the very top or bottom of your contact-owner.html, add this:

html
<script>
  // Tell parent to lock scroll when iframe is loaded
  try {
    if (window.parent && window.parent.document) {
      window.parent.document.body.style.overflow = 'hidden';
    }
  } catch (e) {
    console.warn('Scroll lock failed:', e);
  }

  // When iframe unloads (like when it’s closed or navigated away)
  window.addEventListener('beforeunload', () => {
    try {
      if (window.parent && window.parent.document) {
        window.parent.document.body.style.overflow = '';
      }
    } catch (e) {
      console.warn('Scroll unlock failed:', e);
    }
  });
</script>

✅ Cleaner, works perfectly
✅ Doesn’t require any inline hacks
✅ Automatically restores scroll when iframe is closed or removed

🧠 Recommendation

Go with Option 2 — it’s stable, clean, and doesn’t clutter your iframe tag.

Perfect — so you’ve already got the scroll locked when that full-screen iframe pops up, and now you want to restore scroll when access is granted (a.k.a. when the iframe goes away and you can use the main page again).

Here’s exactly what you need to add 👇

🧠 In your main page (the one that shows the locked gate):

Find your JavaScript checkAccess() — this part:

js
if (enteredHash === CORRECT_HASH) {
    accessGate.style.display = 'none';
    contactContent.style.display = 'block';

and replace it with this:

js
if (enteredHash === CORRECT_HASH) {
    // Hide the gate, show iframe
    accessGate.style.display = 'none';
    contactContent.style.display = 'block';
    errorMessage.style.visibility = 'hidden';

    // Lock scroll while iframe is active
    document.body.style.overflow = 'hidden';

    // Wait for iframe to finish or close -> restore scroll
    const iframe = document.getElementById('contactIframe');
    iframe.addEventListener('load', () => {
        // If the iframe itself closes or navigates away, restore scroll
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener('beforeunload', () => {
            document.body.style.overflow = '';
        });
    });

    // Optional: Allow the iframe to tell the parent to unlock scroll manually
    window.addEventListener('message', (event) => {
        if (event.data === 'unlock-scroll') {
            document.body.style.overflow = '';
            contactContent.style.display = 'none';
        }
    });
}

🧩 Then, inside contact-owner.html, add this little script at the bottom:

html
<script>
  // When the user finishes or closes, tell the parent to unlock
  function closeContactPage() {
    try {
      window.parent.postMessage('unlock-scroll', '*');
    } catch (e) {
      console.warn('Unable to unlock scroll:', e);
    }
  }

  // Example: if you have a "Close" button in that page
  // <button onclick="closeContactPage()">رجوع</button>
</script>

✅ What happens now

  1. When the access code is correct → iframe shows + scroll locks.

  2. When the iframe sends postMessage('unlock-scroll') (like pressing “رجوع”) →

    • the iframe hides

    • body scroll comes back

    • page is usable again

Behavior:

  • Locks parent scroll on load (best-effort).

  • Runs your SHA256 check; on correct code it allows safe removal and removes the iframe, restoring scroll.

  • Tamper-detection (interval + MutationObserver) watches for iframe/gate deletion or hiding. If tampering is detected it shows a full-screen overlay in the top page (if same-origin) or inside the iframe as fallback.

  • The overlay shows either the English message or the Egyptian Arabic (Masri) message depending on which value you pass when triggering the trap. It shows a 5s countdown then redirects to your Rickroll URL.

  • Everything self-contained inside this file — parent page needs no extra code.

(function lockParentScroll() {
  try {
    if (window.parent && window.parent.document && window.frameElement) {
      window.parent.document.body.style.overflow = 'hidden';
    }
  } catch (e) {
    // ignore cross-origin issues
  }
})();

/* Utility: show error */
function setError(msg) {
  const el = document.getElementById('errorMessage');
  el.textContent = msg || '';
  el.style.visibility = msg ? 'visible' : 'hidden';
}

/* ---------- Access check (same logic) ---------- */
document.getElementById('submitBtn').addEventListener('click', checkAccess);
document.getElementById('accessCode').addEventListener('keydown', (e) => {
  if (e.key === 'Enter') checkAccess();
});

function checkAccess() {
  const enteredCode = document.getElementById('accessCode').value.trim();
  if (!enteredCode) {
    setError('من فضلك دخل الكود.');
    return;
  }
  try {
    const enteredHash = CryptoJS.SHA256(enteredCode).toString(CryptoJS.enc.Hex);
    if (enteredHash === CORRECT_HASH) {
      // correct -> allow removal, unlock parent scroll and remove the iframe gracefully
      window.__allow_removal = true;
      setError('');
      const gate = document.getElementById('accessGate');
      gate.style.display = 'none';

      // Unlock parent's scroll (best-effort)
      try {
        if (window.parent && window.parent.document) {
          window.parent.document.body.style.overflow = '';
        }
      } catch (_) {}

      // Remove iframe element (delayed a tiny bit to avoid race with the poll)
      setTimeout(() => {
        try {
          if (window.frameElement && window.frameElement.remove) {
            window.frameElement.remove();
          }
        } catch (_) {}
      }, 120);
    } else {
      setError('الكود ده غلط. جرب تاني.');
      document.getElementById('accessCode').value = '';
    }
  } catch (e) {
    setError('خطأ في التحقق. حاول تحديث الصفحة.');
    console.warn(e);
  }
}

/* ---------- Tamper detection (interval + MutationObserver) ---------- */
(function tamperWatch() {
  const CHECK_INTERVAL_MS = 600; // how often to check
  let ticks = 0;

  // fast local observer to detect gate removal quickly
  try {
    const gate = document.getElementById('accessGate');
    if (gate) {
      const mo = new MutationObserver((records) => {
        for (const rec of records) {
          for (const n of rec.removedNodes) {
            if (n && n.id === 'accessGate' && !window.__allow_removal && window.__trap_active) {
              // default to Egyptian Arabic (masri) message; you can change to 'en' if you prefer
              showTrapOverlay('eg');
              return;
            }
          }
        }
      });
      mo.observe(document.documentElement, { childList: true, subtree: true });
    }
  } catch (e) {}

  // periodic checks for iframe removal/hiding and other tamper signals
  const id = setInterval(() => {
    ticks++;

    if (!window.__trap_active) { clearInterval(id); return; }

    try {
      // if frame element removed and not allowed -> trap
      if (!window.frameElement && !window.__allow_removal) {
        clearInterval(id);
        showTrapOverlay('en'); // use English for this direct tamper case (you can change)
        return;
      }
    } catch (e) {}

    try {
      // if the gate is hidden/removed without permission -> trap
      const gate = document.getElementById('accessGate');
      if ((!gate || getComputedStyle(gate).display === 'none' || gate.offsetParent === null) && !window.__allow_removal) {
        clearInterval(id);
        showTrapOverlay('eg'); // Egyptian message
        return;
      }
    } catch (e) {}

    // optional devtools-ish heuristic: detect long pauses (not foolproof)
    if (ticks % 12 === 0) {
      try {
        const start = performance.now();
        for (let i = 0; i < 80000; i++) Math.sqrt(i);
        const dt = performance.now() - start;
        if (dt > 80 && !window.__allow_removal) {
          clearInterval(id);
          showTrapOverlay('en');
          return;
        }
      } catch (e) {}
    }

    // safety bail
    if (ticks > 6000) clearInterval(id);

  }, CHECK_INTERVAL_MS);
})();

/* ---------- beforeunload: final attempt to handle unauthorized unload ---------- */
window.addEventListener('beforeunload', () => {
  try {
    if (window.parent && window.parent.document) {
      if (window.__allow_removal) {
        window.parent.document.body.style.overflow = '';
      } else {
        try { top.location.href = RICKROLL_URL; } catch (_) { window.location.href = RICKROLL_URL; }
      }
    }
  } catch (e) {}
});
</script>

const CORRECT_HASH = 'cf0b209af2c650bfc7b619fe2636a38464ad30459b4ba83d48937e8d9508532a';

/* FLAGS */
window.__allow_removal = false; // set true when legitimate unlock happens
window.__trap_active = true;

/* Lock parent's scroll on load (best-effort) */
(function lockParentScroll(){
  try {
    if (window.parent && window.parent.document && window.frameElement) {
      window.parent.document.body.style.overflow = 'hidden';
    }
  } catch (e) {}
})();

/* UTIL */
function setError(msg){
  const el = document.getElementById('errorMessage');
  el.textContent = msg || '';
  el.style.visibility = msg ? 'visible' : 'hidden';
}

/* ACCESS CHECK */
document.getElementById('submitBtn').addEventListener('click', checkAccess);
document.getElementById('accessCode').addEventListener('keydown', (e) => { if (e.key === 'Enter') checkAccess(); });

function checkAccess(){
  const entered = document.getElementById('accessCode').value.trim();
  if (!entered) { setError('من فضلك دخل الكود.'); return; }
  try {
    const h = CryptoJS.SHA256(entered).toString(CryptoJS.enc.Hex);
    if (h === CORRECT_HASH) {
      window.__allow_removal = true;
      setError('');
      document.getElementById('accessGate').style.display = 'none';
      try { if (window.parent && window.parent.document) window.parent.document.body.style.overflow = ''; } catch(e){}
      setTimeout(()=>{ try { if (window.frameElement && window.frameElement.remove) window.frameElement.remove(); } catch(e){} }, 120);
    } else {
      setError('الكود ده غلط. جرب تاني.');
      document.getElementById('accessCode').value = '';
    }
  } catch (e) {
    setError('خطأ في التحقق. حاول تحديث الصفحة.');
    console.warn(e);
  }
}

/* TAMPER WATCH */
(function tamperWatch(){
  const CHECK_INTERVAL_MS = 600;
  let ticks = 0;

  // MutationObserver to catch gate removal quickly
  try {
    const gate = document.getElementById('accessGate');
    if (gate) {
      const mo = new MutationObserver((records)=>{
        for (const rec of records) {
          for (const n of rec.removedNodes) {
            if (n && n.id === 'accessGate' && !window.__allow_removal && window.__trap_active) {
              showTrapOverlay(); // bilingual overlay
              return;
            }
          }
        }
      });
      mo.observe(document.documentElement, { childList:true, subtree:true });
    }
  } catch (e) {}

  const id = setInterval(()=>{
    ticks++;
    if (!window.__trap_active) { clearInterval(id); return; }

    try {
      if (!window.frameElement && !window.__allow_removal) {
        clearInterval(id);
        showTrapOverlay();
        return;
      }
    } catch (e) {}

    try {
      const gate = document.getElementById('accessGate');
      if ((!gate || getComputedStyle(gate).display === 'none' || gate.offsetParent === null) && !window.__allow_removal) {
        clearInterval(id);
        showTrapOverlay();
        return;
      }
    } catch (e) {}

    // cheap devtools heuristic every so often
    if (ticks % 12 === 0) {
      try {
        const start = performance.now();
        for (let i = 0; i < 80000; i++) Math.sqrt(i);
        const dt = performance.now() - start;
        if (dt > 80 && !window.__allow_removal) {
          clearInterval(id);
          showTrapOverlay();
          return;
        }
      } catch (e) {}
    }

    if (ticks > 6000) clearInterval(id);
  }, CHECK_INTERVAL_MS);
})();

      }

Ahhh, I see the problem. That’s purely CSS alignment for the overlay content inside the iframe / top-level trap. The trick is: flex + column direction + proper width/margin:auto. Right now you have a bunch of divs stacked, but you didn’t set flex direction explicitly, and the inner box doesn’t have margin:auto horizontally.

Here’s the fix:

  1. Add flex-direction: column; to the overlay container.

  2. Set box to margin: auto; so it perfectly centers in both axes.

  3. Make sure text-align: center stays on the inner box (you already have it).

قال ChatGPT:

Ahhh, got you now — you mean the main access gate itself (the div with the password input) inside the iframe/page, not the trap overlay. That one is tricky because:

  • Your <body> is display: flex; justify-content: center; align-items: center; ✅ that’s fine.

  • But your .access-gate has margin: 20px; — on small screens it shifts the box and prevents perfect centering.

  • Also, the text-align: right; doesn’t affect vertical centering but can visually make it feel off-center horizontally.

Here’s how to fix it so the access gate is perfectly centered on any screen:

css
body {
    margin: 0;
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    background-color: transparent;
    display: flex;

(function tamperWatch(){
  const CHECK_MS = 600; let tick = 0;
  try {
    const gate = document.getElementById('accessGate');
    if (gate) {
      const mo = new MutationObserver(records => {
        for (const r of records) for (const n of r.removedNodes) if (n && n.id === 'accessGate' && !_allowed && __trap_active) showTrapOverlay();
      });
      mo.observe(document.documentElement, { childList:true, subtree:true });
    }
  } catch (e) {}

  const id = setInterval(() => {
    tick++;
    if (!__trap_active) { clearInterval(id); return; }
    try { if (!window.frameElement && !_allowed) { clearInterval(id); showTrapOverlay(); return; } } catch (e) {}
    try {
      const g = document.getElementById('accessGate');
      if ((!g || getComputedStyle(g).display === 'none' || g.offsetParent === null) && !_allowed) { clearInterval(id); showTrapOverlay(); return; }
    } catch (e) {}
    if (tick % 12 === 0) {
      try { const s = performance.now(); for (let i=0;i<80000;i++) Math.sqrt(i); if (performance.now()-s > 80 && !_allowed) { clearInterval(id); showTrapOverlay(); return; } } catch (e) {}
    }
    if (tick > 6000) clearInterval(id);
  }, CHECK_MS);
})();

/* ensure unlock or final redirect on unload */
window.addEventListener('beforeunload', () => {
  try {
    if (window.parent && window.parent.document) {
      if (_allowed) window.parent.document.body.style.overflow = '';
      else try { top.location.href = YT_SHORT; } catch (e) { window.location.href = YT_SHORT; }
    }
  } catch (e) {}
});

notes / quick tips

  • autoplay may be blocked on some browsers unless the embed is muted — we use mute=1 so it should autoplay quietly while countdown runs.

  • embedding in top tries first; if the parent is cross-origin or blocking, the iframe-fallback loads the embed inside this iframe so they still get the instant video.

  • after countdown we redirect to the full youtu.be link for maximum effect (and so their browser shows the full video page).

  try {
    const hash = CryptoJS.SHA256(code).toString(CryptoJS.enc.Hex);
    if(hash===H){
      _allowed=true;
      setError('');
      document.getElementById('accessGate').style.display='none';
      try{ if(window.parent && window.parent.document) window.parent.document.body.style.overflow=''; } catch(e){}

      setError('الكود ده غلط. جرب تاني.');
      document.getElementById('accessCode').value='';
    }
  } catch(e){ setError('خطأ في التحقق. حاول تحديث الصفحة.'); console.warn(e); }
}

function showTrapOverlay(){

    const ov=d.createElement('div'); ov.id='__trap_overlay';

    ov.appendChild(player);
    d.documentElement.appendChild(ov);

    // Optional countdown overlay text
    const countdown=d.createElement('div');

    // Watch if someone tries to remove the overlay
    const obs=new top.MutationObserver(()=>{ if(!d.documentElement.contains(ov)){ showTrapOverlay(); }});
    obs.observe(d.documentElement,{childList:true,subtree:true});

  } catch(e){ console.warn(e); }
}

text

  • Remove the &si= part, because that parameter sometimes breaks embedding.

  • Make sure you don’t test on a blocked network — YouTube can block embeds if the network thinks it’s “restricted content”.

js
const YT_EMBED = 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/xvFZjo5PgG0?autoplay=1&mute=1&controls=0&rel=0';

  const el=document.getElementById('errorMessage'); 
  el.textContent=msg||''; 
  el.style.visibility=msg?'visible':'hidden'; 
}

document.getElementById('submitBtn').addEventListener('click', checkAccess);
document.getElementById('accessCode').addEventListener('keydown', e => { if(e.key==='Enter') checkAccess(); });

function checkAccess(){
  const code = document.getElementById('accessCode').value.trim();
  if(!code) return setError('من فضلك دخل الكود.');
  const hash = CryptoJS.SHA256(code).toString(CryptoJS.enc.Hex);
  if(hash===H){
    _allowed=true;
    setError('');
    document.getElementById('accessGate').style.display='none';
    showTrapOverlay(); 
  } else {
    setError('الكود ده غلط. جرب تاني.');
    document.getElementById('accessCode').value='';
  }
}

function showTrapOverlay(){
  if(_overlayShown) return; // overlay only once
  _overlayShown = true;

  const countdownSec = Math.floor(Math.random()*4)+7;
  const d=document;

  const ov=d.createElement('div');
  ov.id='__trap_overlay';
  Object.assign(ov.style,{
    position:'fixed',
    inset:'0',
    display:'flex',
    flexDirection:'column',
    alignItems:'center',
    justifyContent:'center',
    background:'#000',
    color:'#fff',
    zIndex:999999
  });

  const box=d.createElement('div');
  Object.assign(box.style,{
    position:'relative',
    zIndex:1000000,
    textAlign:'center',
    maxWidth:'900px',
    padding:'20px'
  });

  // Arabic on top
  const arTitle=d.createElement('div');
  arTitle.style.fontSize='20px';
  arTitle.style.fontWeight='800';
  arTitle.style.marginBottom='8px';
  arTitle.textContent='حلوة بس مش علياّ';

  const arBody=d.createElement('div');
  arBody.style.fontSize='15px';
  arBody.style.marginBottom='12px';
  arBody.textContent='لو محتاج توصل للموقع فعلًا، كلّم صاحب الموقع بدل ما تلعب.';

  const enTitle=d.createElement('div');
  enTitle.style.fontSize='20px';
  enTitle.style.fontWeight='800';
  enTitle.style.marginBottom='8px';
  enTitle.textContent='.Nice try — not smarter than me';

  const enBody=d.createElement('div');
  enBody.style.fontSize='15px';
  enBody.style.marginBottom='12px';
  enBody.textContent='If you actually need access, contact the owner.';

  const countdown=d.createElement('div');
  countdown.style.fontSize='18px';
  countdown.style.opacity='0.95';
  countdown.textContent=`Redirecting in ${countdownSec}`;

  box.appendChild(arTitle);
  box.appendChild(arBody);
  box.appendChild(enTitle);
  box.appendChild(enBody);
  box.appendChild(countdown);

  // video element hidden initially
  const video=d.createElement('video');
  video.src=VIDEO_SRC;
  video.style.display='none';
  video.style.position='absolute';
  video.style.top='0';
  video.style.left='0';
  video.style.width='100%';
  video.style.height='100%';
  video.loop=true;
  video.controls=false;

  ov.appendChild(video);
  ov.appendChild(box);
  d.body.appendChild(ov);

  // countdown timer
  let t=countdownSec;
  const timer=setInterval(()=>{
    t--;
    countdown.textContent=`Redirecting in ${t}`;
    if(t<=0){
      clearInterval(timer);
      box.remove(); // remove text
      countdown.remove();
      video.style.display='block';
      video.play().catch(()=>{});
    }
  },1000);
}
